util.validation

Interface ObjectParser<T>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    SingleTokenParserAdapter, TwoTokenParser

    public interface ObjectParser<T>
    Turns a textual representation of a T-value into an instance of T.

        Parses a textual representation of a T-value.
        Parameters:

      • withValidation

        default ObjectParser<T> withValidation(Validator<java.lang.String,T> validator)
        Combines this parser with a validator. First applies this parser to turn tokens into a T-value, then the given validator decides if the parsed value is legit. If this parser fails, then the process stops there and the parse error is returned; otherwise the parsed value is given to the validator. If validation fails, then the validation error is returned; otherwise the parsed value is returned.
        Parameters:
        validator - the validation to apply to the parsed value.
        Returns:
        a parser that uses this object to do the parsing and then applies the given validator to the parsed result.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the argument is null.
